                <head>196. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On March 3, <persName corresp="#p_BLE1">Loftus Becker</persName> sent to Acting
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName> a memorandum entitled
                    “Questions Relating to Berlin Contingency Planning,” which covered the legal
                    aspects of planning for Berlin. (<persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_WAC1"
                        >Whitman</persName> File, Administration Series)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
